  "text": "Since the identification of NOD2 as the first CD susceptibility gene in 2001, the three main NOD2 mutations p.Arg702Trp, p.Gly908Arg, and p.Leu1007fsX1008 still represent the most strongly CD-associated variants [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In a study of Lesage et al. [CITATION_4] , the rare NOD2 variant IVS4+10 A>C (rs72796353) was only found in CD, suggesting its suitability as a predictor for CD susceptibility.",
